Rubio, like many of his cohorts are quick to assert "that our rights come from our creator."  While there is a constitutional reference to "the Creator" as being the source of our rights, the president should only be concerned with those rights conferred upon us by the Constitution itself and clarified by justices charged with interpreting the Founders words.

Even when those rights conflict with her personal, religious beliefs.  Enforcing fundamental interpretations of God's law is best left to those most qualified, like the Supreme Leader of Iran and the Taliban.

Donald Trump reprised his role as birther by questioning Ted Cruz's eligibility to be president, just as he did with Barack Obama.

In case you haven't heard, Ted Cruz was born in Canada.

I question Marco Rubio's eligibility to be president, and not because his parents didn't become citizens until after little baby Marco was born.  (What, you didn't know that Marco was an anchor baby?)

I question Marco Rubio's eligibility to be president because I'm not sure on what planet he was born.

